relation: There was face-painting on the chartered train to The Wave, as well as knitting, and adapted carols.
The DCGA banner was in a sea of other banners and placards during the march.
Our destination, aiming to put pressure on politicians to negotiate a Fair, Ambitious and Binding deal at Copenhagen.
The south west contingent in the back streets between Paddington and Hyde Park.
There was also beard-painting on the train!
Arrival of the southwest contingent at Paddington. There were 450 on the train, chartered by CAFOD, Tearfund, Friends of the Earth and Christian Aid.

More than 50,000 people marched from Grosvenor Square, through Mayfair, along Piccadilly, past Eros and Trafalgar Square, along Whitehall, and around Westminster on the bridges and both sides of the river.
